Russian Equity Movers: Rosneft, Lukoil, PIK Group, AvtoVAZ

-- B y   J a c k   J o r d a n   a n d   M a r k   S w e e t m a n
-- 
2011-05-12T15:19:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-12/russian-equity-movers-rosneft-sberbank-pik-group-rosinter.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  slid 1.5
percent to 1,630.78 at the 6:45 p.m. close in Moscow, the lowest
level since Dec. 1. The dollar-denominated RTS Index lost 2.3
percent to 1,864.95.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO  AvtoVAZ (AVAZ)   snapped three days of gains,
declining 0.7 percent to 26.879 rubles.  Russia ’s largest
automaker should waive dividends for 2010 after returning to
profit from a loss in 2009, Chairman  Sergei Chemezov  told
reporters in Togliatti, Russia, late yesterday.  OAO Rosneft (ROSN RX), Russia’s biggest oil producer,
retreated for a second day, falling 0.7 percent to 231.4 rubles.
Crude for June delivery declined as much as $2.96 to $95.25 per
barrel. OAO Lukoil (LKOH RX) and OAO Gazprom Neft (SIBN RX) lost
2.9 percent to 1,726.3 rubles and 4.2 percent to 124.36 rubles,
respectively.  OAO Polymetal (PMTL RX), the Russian precious-metals
producer, retreated 4.9 percent to 457 rubles, the lowest
closing price since Oct. 1. Silver and gold for immediate
delivery both declined for a second day.  PIK Group (PIKK)  , a Russian real-estate developer,
declined a second day, retreating 2.3 percent to 108.53 rubles.
The board recommended shareholders waive 2010 dividends, the
company said in a regulatory filing late yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
